      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Add the {{chicken-thigh}}, {{olives-green}}, {{onion}}, {{garlic}}, {{ginger-root}}, {{cumin-ground}}, {{coriander-ground}}, {{turmeric}}, {{sea-salt-fine}}, and {{black-pepper}} to the slow cooker. Pour in the {{stock-chicken}}. Cook on low for 4.5 to 5.5 hours. Add the {{preserved-lemon}} rind in the last 30 minutes. Taste before adding further salt, the preserved lemon and olives contribute salt throughout the cook. Serve with couscous, yoghurt, and fresh herbs.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "troubleshooter",
        "attrs": {
          "items": [
            {
              "fix": "Add preserved lemon in the last 30 minutes only. Rinse brine-packed olives before adding. Taste before seasoning, this dish rarely needs added salt",
              "cause": "Preserved lemon added too early and dissolved into the sauce, or olives are very salty",
              "symptom": "Dish tastes overly salty"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Stir in a little fresh preserved lemon rind after cooking. Even a small amount added at the end provides a clear citrus note",
              "cause": "Added from the beginning and lost its brightness",
              "symptom": "Preserved lemon flavour not coming through"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Reduce the stock to 150 ml. The chicken releases moisture during the cook so less stock than expected is needed",
              "cause": "Too much stock",
              "symptom": "Sauce too thin"
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Where this dish lives",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Moroccan chicken with olives and preserved lemon is one of the most elegant slow-cooker chicken dishes in terms of flavour complexity for effort. The three key flavours (the spice base, the olives, and the preserved lemon) do the work. Serve with couscous mixed with toasted flaked almonds and dried apricots for a full Moroccan table.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
